20/09/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The trial of members of a group led by alleged drug trafficker Darko Saric is expected to open on Monday (September 20th) in Belgrade. In all, 20 people are charged with smuggling 2.5 tonnes of cocaine from South America last year. Saric and six others remain at large. If convicted, the defendants could face up to 40 years in prison. (Beta, Vecernje Novosti, Blic - 19/09/10)
